<div id="welcome-panel" class="container">
  <h2>Events in and around Sanderstead</h2>
</div>
<div class="container" id="main-wrapper">
  <div class="row main-content">
    <div class="col-md-12 white-column">
      <h2>Latest events for 2015</h2>
      <table>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a name="reading"></a>Autumn at Sanderstead Library</h3>
              <p>We hope you have had a great summer. Children have until <b>Saturday 12th September 2015</b> to finish off the Summer Reading Challenge in all Croydon Libraries, make sure you get your medal and certificate.</p>
              <p>Special event at the library: Jack and the Beanstalk stories and crafts, <b>Tuesday 25th August, 3.00-4.00pm</b>.</p>
              <p>Wednesday Rhymetimes, 10.30-11.00am and Wiggle and Jiggles, 11.30-12 noon will take place all summer. Wednesday storytime will start again in the week beginning 31st August.</p>
              <p><b>Tuesday 15th September, 3.00-4.00pm,</b> a talk about Priory Farm in nearby Nutfield, by Gordon Gillett, please book a free place.</p>
              <p>All our regular activities for children and adults start again in September and include Storytime, Rhymetime, Wiggle and Jiggle Arty Crafty, Adult Reading Group, Knit and Natter groups etc. For more information please see <%= link_to "Croydon Libraries website", "http://www.croydonlibraries.com/" %> or email <%= mail_to"Croydon.sandersteadlibrary@Carillionservices.co.uk" %>, tel 020 3700 1015.</p>
            </td>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><%= link_to "Croydon Libraries", "http://www.croydonlibraries.com/" %></h3>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a name="cakes"></a>Cake in the Park, 10th September from 10 am</h3>
              <p>There is to be a  ‘CAKE IN THE PARK’ event on Thursday 10th of September, between 10am and 12.30. The cake ladies of Purley Beeches will be busy baking cakes and bringing them to the Beeches to raise funds for the Macmillan Charity, a very worthwhile cause and although not an official FOPB activity, well worth supporting. Our doggy companions won’t be forgotten either, as treats will be provided for them as well. Please bring appetite, funds and maybe a container to take some cake home. For more information please contact Mac Court <%= mail_to "mac@skyy.me.uk" %>. Click the link to download a form to join the <%= link_to "Friends of Purley Beeches", "/resource/purley_beeches_enrol.pdf" %>.</p>
            </td>
            <td class="events">
              <%= link_to image_tag("small-images/purley_beeches100.jpg", alt: "Purley Beeches logo"), "/resource/purley_beeches_enrol.pdf" %>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a name="pond"></a>Work day at Hamsey Green pond, 12th September 10 am</h3>
              <p>Peter Underwood from The Conservation Volunteers has confirmed the date for a work day at Hamsey Green Pond. Please do come along and help on Saturday, 12 September at 10.00 am. </p>
              <p> The work will involve clearing up any further litter and a cleaning out of the silt traps.  It is only for a few hours finishing at 1pm with a nice cup of tea.  Do wear your wellingtons.  Some equipment will be provided.</p>
            </td>
            <td class="events">
              <%= link_to image_tag("http://www.tcv.org.uk/sites/all/themes/tcvmain/images/logo.png", alt: "TCV logo"), "http://www.tcv.org.uk/" %>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a name="funhour"></a>Family Fun Hour for little ones and their families, 13th September 3 - 4 pm</h3>
              <p>One hour of crafts, Bible stories, singing and tea for parents and young children. Held in All Saints Halls, Onslow Gardens. Future dates: 11th October and 8th November. For more infomation please visit the parish website, <%= link_to "www.sanderstead-parish.org.uk", "http:www.sanderstead-parish.org.uk" %> or contact Rev Martin Greenfield 020  8657 1366, <%= mail_to "rector@sanderstead-parish.org.uk" %>. </p>
            </td>
            <td class="events">
              <%= link_to image_tag("small-images/all_saints100.jpg", alt: "All Saints logo"), "http://www.sanderstead-parish.org.uk/all-saints" %>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a name="fopb19sep"></a>Friends Of Purley Beeches working party, 19th September</h3>
              <p>Working party in Purley Beeches from 10 am to 2 pm. Tools, hot drinks and light refreshments will be provided. If you haven't attended a previous work party, please don't be put off. come for as long or as little time that you can spare, but please wear suitable cloting, stout footwear and tough gardening clothes. For more information please contact Mac Court <%= mail_to "mac@skyy.me.uk" %>. Click the link to download a form to join the <%= link_to "Friends of Purley Beeches", "/resource/purley_beeches_enrol.pdf" %>.</p>
            </td>
            <td class="events">
              <%= link_to image_tag("small-images/purley_beeches100.jpg", alt: "Purley Beeches logo"), "/resource/purley_beeches_enrol.pdf" %>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a name="priscilla"></a>Priscilla's Community Fun Day on the Rec, Saturday 26th September, 11 am - 4 pm</h3>
              <p>Priscilla's Tea Room are hosting another Sanderstead Community Day at Sanderstead Recreation Ground on Saturday, 26th September from 11 till 4.
              Local businesses, service providers and Charities will be showcasing what they do and providing lots of things that you can buy and experience. Some great people from last year will be back including Kingsmead Equestrian Centre, Zorbit UK inflatables, Croydon Drop in, Sams Fun Faces and many more. And some new faces from Cook Sanderstead, Veg Out, Priscilla's knitting club and many more. If your local business would like to take part by being at the event or donating to the raffle, please contact us on <%= mail_to "priscillastearoom@outlook.com" %> or pop in to the tea room to see us.</p>
            </td>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><%= link_to image_tag("small-images/priscillas.jpg", alt: "Priscilla's Tearoom"), "http://priscillastearoom.co.uk/" %></h3>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a name="fopb17oct"></a>Friends Of Purley Beeches working party, 17th October</h3>
              <p>Working party in Purley Beeches from 10 am to 2 pm. Tools, hot drinks and light refreshments will be provided. If you haven't attended a previous work party, please don't be put off. come for as long or as little time that you can spare, but please wear suitable cloting, stout footwear and tough gardening clothes. For more information please contact Mac Court <%= mail_to "mac@skyy.me.uk" %>. Click the link to download a form to join the <%= link_to "Friends of Purley Beeches", "/resource/purley_beeches_enrol.pdf" %>.</p>
            </td>
